	(text "SEC 7  INPUT PROTECTION + FAIL-OPEN MODE (active). Q20/Q21 DN2540 depletion pair (norm-ON, ~3R each) in HI leg; Rg holds Vgs=0. HI_P clamp Q22/Q23 (2N4117A) to STAR. On |HI_P|>~0.4V window comp U22 sets latch U23 -> trip SSR U21 pulls GPROT to -12V => FETs OFF (true disconnect). K5 DELETED: mode via SSR pairs U24/U25 (direct HI_P->CH_A) + U26/U27 (LO_F->STAR); DIRECT_L high = direct mode; bridge U4-U11 (ex BR_HI/LO now HI_P/LO_F) = chop mode; BOTH normally-open => input isolated when unpowered. TBD/VERIFY: (a) U22 window thresh R51-54 + LM2903 input-CM must tolerate HI_P to -0.6V and OD level (may need gnd-ref comp or level-shift); (b) RESET_N clears trip latch at power-up; (c) DN2540 Idss sets pre-trip surge into Q22/Q23 & bridge - check AQY221N2M pulse rating; (d) noise: Q20/Q21 Ron adds ~0.32nV/rtHz."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
